                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1293">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/41.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Vice Consul <persName type="to">Guyant</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 8th. Make urgent protest against any attempt to exact forced loans
                    from foreigners. If, however, authorities persist in attempt, advise foreigners
                    to pay under protest, making protest a matter of record if possible, and to
                    secure receipts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
